NPA head Shaun Abrahams has been invited to appear before the committee at a meeting set down for Friday morning. CAPE TOWN - National Prosecutions Authority (NPA) chief Shaun Abrahams is set to appear before Parliament s justice committee on Friday.The call for him to brief the committee comes after his about-turn over the decision to prosecute Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan and two former Sars executives for fraud.Abrahams announced the withdrawal of the charges yesterday, on the eve of planned demonstrations in support of Gordhan.Justice committee chairperson Mathole Motshekga says the committee wants to be briefed by the NPA head as soon as possible.He says Abrahams has been invited to appear before the committee at a meeting set down for Friday morning.If the National Director of Public Prosecutions accepts the invitation, he could find himself in the hot seat.He will face a barrage of questions from MPs about his handling of the case against the Finance Minister and two former Sars officials and his decision to drop charges that many legal experts maintain should never have been brought in the first place.WATCH: Shaun Abrahams on political capture, charging a president &amp; more(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)